<P><FONT SIZE=+1>ARCO (Atlantic Richfield Company) and its affiliates operate globally in all aspects of the energy business: the
exploration, production and marketing of crude oil, natural gas and natural
gas liquids, and the refining, marketing and transportation of petroleum
products.</FONT>
<P>ARCO has interests in chemicals and coal and has created a variety of businesses ancillary
to
its operations, including retail convenience stores, cogeneration of steam
and electricity, and electronic payment systems. ARCO's earliest predecessor,
The Atlantic Petroleum Storage Company, was founded on July 1, 1866, in
Pennsylvania.
<P>ARCO has&nbsp;maintained a tradition of excellence and has established
itself as a leader in the industry. ARCO makes environmental sensitivity
and community concern an integral part of its business everywhere it
operates.
